class Solution {
    public int isPrefixOfWord(String sentence, String searchWord) {
        String[] words = sentence.split(" ");
        for (int i = 0; i < words.length; i++) {
            if (words[i].startsWith(searchWord)) {
                return i + 1;
            }
        }
        return -1;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n*m)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution splits the sentence into words and checks each word to see if it starts with the searchWord. It returns the index of the first matching word (1-indexed). The time complexity is O(n*m) due to the split operation and the startsWith check, where n is the number of words and m is the average length of a word. The space complexity is O(n) for storing the words array.
